From: Radhey Shyam Pandey <radhey.shyam.pandey@xilinx.com>
Date: Mon, 26 May 2014 17:02:29 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 269/456] media: xilinx: Fix error handling

This patch comes from:
  https://github.com/Xilinx/linux-xlnx.git

Fix error handling in xvip_graph_dma_init()
Avoid multiple free of vb2 dma context

Signed-off-by: Radhey Shyam Pandey <radheys@xilinx.com>
Signed-off-by: Michal Simek <michal.simek@xilinx.com>
(cherry picked from commit dad92bdb548f84906033c56f6960c15b7aaa6eea)
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-dma.c |    5 +++--
 1 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-dma.c b/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-dma.c
index e550938..17a433e 100644
--- a/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-dma.c
+++ b/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-dma.c
@@ -980,7 +980,6 @@ int xvip_dma_init(struct xvip_composite_device *xdev, struct xvip_dma *dma,
 	return 0;
 
 error:
-	vb2_dma_contig_cleanup_ctx(dma->alloc_ctx);
 	xvip_dma_cleanup(dma);
 	return ret;
 }
@@ -993,7 +992,9 @@ void xvip_dma_cleanup(struct xvip_dma *dma)
 	if (dma->dma)
 		dma_release_channel(dma->dma);
 
-	vb2_dma_contig_cleanup_ctx(dma->alloc_ctx);
+	if (!IS_ERR_OR_NULL(dma->alloc_ctx))
+		vb2_dma_contig_cleanup_ctx(dma->alloc_ctx);
+
 	media_entity_cleanup(&dma->video.entity);
 
 	mutex_destroy(&dma->lock);
